  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Gather Materials",
      "body": "Mark cut lines on the plywood using the cut list as your guide.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/10919ed0330bdb32.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Cut Plywood",
      "body": "Using a circular saw and Kreg rip-cut, cut the plywood. Spend extra time making sure everything is lined up and even. The Kreg rip-cut helps make very straight cuts.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/96ed75421a6f3f68.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Sand Edges",
      "body": "Dry fit pieces into place making adjustment if needed.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/4e118567c01457c9.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Mark Picture and Handle Locations",
      "body": "Okay, this next step needs to be kept organized. If you would like to add personalized pictures, like in our example, you will need to mark those four squares as they won’t be getting stain. We did this with post-it notes. Also mark the edges that will get a handle.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/621bc41b6b824dcf.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Stain or Paint",
      "body": "Stain all pieces except the ones that will have the transferred pictures. Let dry.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/0f777e2cd3c25648.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Apply Pictures",
      "body": "If adding pictures, apply to wood now. See extras for tutorial.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/63422ddee7341a3d.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Attach handles",
      "body": "Use the Kreg cabinet hardware jig to add the handles before assembling boxes.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/45815ea87c9d5553.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Assemble Boxes",
      "body": "Dry fit your box pieces again and hold or clamp pieces into place. Add glue, then use nails to secure all sides.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/e79f48c0c8ff21bf.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Add Hinges",
      "body": "Mark the placement of the hinges. Place one hinge on front and another on opposite side back. See cover photos for example. Drill pilot holes, screw into place.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/df06771310fcec6c.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Add Plants or Herbs",
      "body": "Fill with your favorite potted flowers or herbs. Get creative and customize to your mom’s favs!",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/3c906bc6d8e77c79.webp"
    }
  ],
